06/08/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- The 13th Serious Crimes Court in Istanbul accepted a third indictment in the so-called Ergenekon case Wednesday (August 5th) The 1,454-page document was submitted earlier this month and indicts 52 people, some of whom are already on trial for allegedly forming or joining a terrorist organisation and using force and violence to impede the government. 
The first hearing in this latest indictment is a month away. 
A fourth and final indictment is expected in the coming months, this time focusing only on top army personnel who allegedly planned to overthrow the ruling Justice and Development Party (AKP) government. 
(Zaman - 06/08/09; Sabah, Reuters, Anadolu news agency, Xinhua - 05/08/09)
